        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 5:38PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bridgeport Reservoir, or 7 miles north of Bridgeport. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Rapidly shifting wind gusts up to 40 mph possible near
Bridgeport Reservoir.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Bridgeport Reservoir, and Bridgeport-Bryant Field
Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
